## Package Manager
- Using **{{packageManager}}** — always use `{{packageManager}}` commands

{{#if hasTypeScript}}
## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled — no `any` types, no `@ts-ignore`
- Use type inference where possible, explicit types for function signatures
- Shared types in the common package, not duplicated
{{/if}}

## Coding Conventions
{{#if (includes technologies "React")}}
- Functional components only, hooks for all state management
- Props interface defined and exported above each component
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "Next.js")}}
- App Router conventions: page.tsx, layout.tsx, loading.tsx, error.tsx
- Server Components by default — add 'use client' only when needed
- Server Actions for mutations
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "Express")}}
- Route handlers are thin — business logic in service modules
- Error handling middleware catches all errors
- Request validation with Zod before processing
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "PostGraphile")}}
- PostGraphile auto-generates the GraphQL API
- Custom mutations via SQL functions (SECURITY DEFINER only when needed)
- Smart tags in .postgraphile.tags.json5 for schema customization
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "Relay")}}
- Relay fragments co-located with components
- usePaginationFragment for all lists
- Optimistic updates for user-initiated mutations
{{/if}}

## Database
{{#if (includes technologies "PostgreSQL (pg)")}}
- Row Level Security on every table
- Migrations must have up() AND down()
- EXPLAIN ANALYZE queries touching >10k rows
- JSONB only for truly schemaless data
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "Redis")}}
- Redis for caching, sessions, and rate limiting
- Always set TTL on cached values
- Use cache-aside pattern, not write-through
{{/if}}

## Testing
{{#if (includes technologies "Vitest")}}
- Vitest for unit and integration tests
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "Jest")}}
- Jest for unit and integration tests  
{{/if}}
{{#if (includes technologies "Playwright")}}
- Playwright for E2E tests
{{/if}}
- Tests live next to source: foo.ts → foo.test.ts
- Arrange-Act-Assert pattern
- Mock external services, not your own code

## Commands
- Install: `{{packageManager}} install`
- Dev: `{{packageManager}} run dev`
- Test: `{{packageManager}} test`
- Build: `{{packageManager}} run build`
- Lint: `{{packageManager}} run lint`

## Don'ts
- Never commit .env files
- Never use `any` type
- Never push to main directly
- Never skip tests for "quick fixes"